
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-align` baraye behtar kardane keyfiyat chap dar printer-haye HP estefade mishavad. In dastoor sar-haye chap ra moratab mikonad ta rang-ha va khatoot be dorosti chap shavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-align -i`  --> ❓ Rahandazi dastoor be soorate interactive (soal az shoma va rahnamayi)
    🔹 `hp-align -g`  --> 🖼️ Rahandazi dastoor be soorate graphical (ba estefade az panjere grafik)
    🔹 `hp-align -u`  --> 🖥️ Rahandazi dastoor be soorate automatic (bedoone dakhalat shoma)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-align -i

    🔹 Rahandazi dastoor `hp-align` be soorate interactive.

    $ hp-align -g

    🔹 Rahandazi dastoor `hp-align` be soorate graphical.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-align -u

    🔹 Printer be soorate khodkar (automatic) sar-haye chap ra moratab mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-align` command is used to improve print quality on HP printers. This command aligns the print heads to ensure colors and lines are printed correctly.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-align -i`  --> ❓ Run the command in interactive mode (prompts you for input and provides guidance)
    🔹 `hp-align -g`  --> 🖼️ Run the command in graphical mode (using a graphical window)
    🔹 `hp-align -u`  --> 🖥️ Run the command in automatic mode (without user intervention)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-align -i

    🔹 Runs the `hp-align` command in interactive mode.

    $ hp-align -g

    🔹 Runs the `hp-align` command in graphical mode.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-align -u

    🔹 The printer automatically aligns the print heads.

